-- Higher Irish Corporate Tax Rate Not a Condition for Bailout, Sarkozy Says
-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 2010-11-20T12:33:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-20/higher-irish-corporate-tax-rate-not-a-condition-for-bailout-sarkozy-says.html
French President Nicolas Sarkozy
said Ireland won’t be forced to raise it’s 12.5 percent
corporate-tax rate as a condition for aid from the European
Union. He spoke to reporters today in Lisbon, where he attended
the NATO summit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Viscusi in Paris at 
 gviscusi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
